## Validation Commands

```bash
# Check if a file is ignored
git check-ignore -v path/to/file

# List all ignored files
git status --ignored

# Test pattern against files
git check-ignore -v --no-index *

# Debug why file isn't ignored
git check-ignore -v --non-matching path/to/file
```

## Common Negation Patterns

Sometimes you need to include a file that would otherwise be ignored:

```gitignore
# Ignore all .env files except the example
.env*
!.env.example

# Ignore dist but keep .gitkeep
dist/*
!dist/.gitkeep

# Ignore vendor except specific package
vendor/*
!vendor/important-package/
```

## Integration Notes

- `.gitignore` in root applies to entire repo
- Subdirectory `.gitignore` files extend root patterns
- Already-tracked files aren't affected (use `git rm --cached`)
- Check in `.gitignore` to version control (don't ignore it!)
